snippet.textDisplay: I know a lot of people rag on her but I’m glad she shared her story. I’m a recovering heroin addict as well and around the same age as Taylor and watching her go to IOP and be on maintenance just like I am gave me a huge sense of comfort. Addiction can take over anyone’s life, it doesn’t care about your social status, race, or how “great” your life is. No one chooses to become an addict, the initial choice to use is there but many people can use recreationally without issues. Addicts live and breathe for the next high. I wish her the best in her journey to recovery.

snippet.textDisplay: The more I look into this story the more petty it seems to be. I'm sorry but coming from someone who also has a history of opiate addiction including heroin this just makes me sick. She's literally making herself out to be the victim in this situation when literally every fucking addict has their own story! You literally chose to do it!!! I get it, your bf was an asshole, abusive, manipulative, etc. and you think your story is somehow unique?  Do you know how many girls out there have the EXACT SAME STORY with the EXACT SAME SCENARIO?! Literally, almost all of them! But he didn't hold you down and force the needle in your arm. You made that choice yourself regardless of how convincing he was. Everyone who has done heroin was in some way or another introduced to it usually by a person that they trusted in some way or another. So don't make this out to be all of your ex's fault as you make your own decisions in life regardless of how stupid they are and you have to live with them! So you went off to get clean and when you get out you find out that your "ex" decided to move on and get with another girl. You then decide to contact said girl in order to "warn" her of how manipulative/bad of a person he actually is and when she doesn't want to listen you get upset and decide to turn around and air out all of your personal relationship problems onto the internet including all of their real info/names and claim that you did it in order to help others and "heal" yourself. It's really not hard to stand back and see this for what it actually is. I'm in no way trying to make your ex out to be innocent in all of this as I'm sure he's far from it but don't advertise it like you are trying to assure that it doesn't happen to any other girls and that it's a step in the healing process. You might accomplish that but it's just a mere side effect of what's really going on here AKA you getting hurt and trying to run your ex's name through the mud to assure that his career is over and that he never gets with another girl again. If this was about you healing yourself you wouldn't have made it public or at least not mention any real names. You did all you possibly could when you tried to contact the girl and telling her but you got vengeful as soon as she chose to ignore it. You should have just stopped there and gone on with your life. Congratulations on being a perfect example of everything wrong with Cancel Culture.
